Interface IndexedNeighborGraphTool.StringConverter

  • Enclosing class:
    IndexedNeighborGraphTool

    public static interface IndexedNeighborGraphTool.StringConverter
    A helper interface for translating vertex elements of a graph to Strings. For a graph whose vertices are of some type T, an implementation of this interface for use by the class IndexedNeighborGraphTool will typically return a String representation for any object of type T.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String asString(java.lang.Object t)
      Returns a String representation of the object t, if there is one.

    • Method Detail

      • asString

        java.lang.String asString(java.lang.Object t)
        Returns a String representation of the object t, if there is one. Otherwise this method returns an empty String.
        Parameters:
        t - any object
        Returns:
        A String representation of t, if it is defined; otherwise returns any empty String.
